'''Ernst Mohr''' ([[20 April]] [[1910]] â€“ [[16 May]] [[1989]]) was a professor for mechanical engineering at the University of [[Wuppertal]]. He developed a [[meteorology|meteorological]] [[rocket]], the [[Mohr Rocket]], on behalf of the German Rocket Society.  The [[Mohr rocket|rocket]] was first launched successfully on [[September 14]], [[1958]] near [[Cuxhaven]].

At the first successful test the rocket proved it could reach heights of 50 kilometers and send out its payload at speeds of 1.2 km per second. 

